Bug 1649402 - Fix thread resorting on new messages for Received sort and sort_threads_by_root. r=mkmelin


When a new message header is added to a threaded db view, its parent thread
should be moved to the correct position if the view is sorted by date/received
and the incoming message is the newest in that thread.

Previously, this automatic re-sorting mechanism was only enabled when sorting
by "Date" (nsMsgViewSortType::byDate). As a result, users sorting by "Received"
would see new messages appear within a thread, but the thread itself would not
bump to the top of the message list until the view was manually refreshed.

Additionally, the live-update logic previously ignored the hidden preference
`mailnews.sort_threads_by_root` (introduced in Bug 495946). If a user set this
preference to keep threads anchored chronologically by their oldest root message,
incoming replies would still incorrectly force the thread to jump to the top.

This patch extends the sorting check in `nsMsgThreadedDBView::OnNewHeader`
to include `nsMsgViewSortType::byReceived`. It also adds a check for
`!mSortThreadsByRoot` to both `nsMsgThreadedDBView` and `nsMsgSearchDBView`
(unified folders), ensuring that live-updates respect the user's thread sorting
preferences across all folder types.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D299224

diff --git a/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp b/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp
--- a/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp
+++ b/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp
@@ -458,18 +458,19 @@ nsresult nsMsgSearchDBView::AddHdrFromFo
         // Not really OK, but not failure exactly.
         return NS_OK;
       }
 
       NS_ASSERTION(!m_levels[threadIndex],
                    "threadRoot incorrect, or level incorrect");
 
       bool moveThread = false;
-      if (m_sortType == nsMsgViewSortType::byDate ||
-          m_sortType == nsMsgViewSortType::byReceived) {
+      if ((m_sortType == nsMsgViewSortType::byDate ||
+           m_sortType == nsMsgViewSortType::byReceived) &&
+          !mSortThreadsByRoot) {
         uint32_t newestMsgInThread = 0, msgDate = 0;
         viewThread->GetNewestMsgDate(&newestMsgInThread);
         msgHdr->GetDateInSeconds(&msgDate);
         moveThread = (msgDate == newestMsgInThread);
       }
 
       OrExtraFlag(threadIndex,
                   MSG_VIEW_FLAG_HASCHILDREN | MSG_VIEW_FLAG_ISTHREAD);
